Christopher Daykin (born July 18, 1948) CB is a Fellow of the Institute of Actuaries and was the Government Actuary for the United Kingdom from 1989 to 2007. He is the second longest holder of the post. He was president of the Institute of Actuaries between 1994 and 1996. He was awarded a CB. He was presented with an Honorary Doctor of Science from City University London 1995 http://www.city.ac.uk/alumni Daykin has published reports on issues such as the state pension scheme and co-authored the book Practical Risk Theory for Actuaries (ISBN 0-412-42850-4).   == Early life == He has a first class mathematics degree from Pembroke College, Cambridge University and attended Merchant Taylors' School, London.   == See also == Government Actuary's Department Institute of Actuaries   == References ==
